================================================================================
SUMMARY & RECOMMENDATIONS
================================================================================

FINDINGS:
  1. Post-hoc power for observed Δr = 0.010: 0.409 (UNDERPOWERED)
  2. N required for 0.80 power: 1050 (IMPRACTICAL)
  3. Power for meaningful Δr = 0.05: 1.000
  4. Ceiling effect: r_full = 0.934, headroom = 0.066 (STRONG)
  5. Destination shows larger effect due to more headroom

CONCLUSION:
  Source correlation null finding (Δr = 0.010, p_bonf = 0.172)
  is BEST EXPLAINED by CEILING EFFECT, NOT inadequate power.

  Evidence:
    - Full CTT r = 0.934 leaves only 0.066 headroom
    - Observed Δr = 0.010 uses 15.4% of available headroom
    - Destination memory (r_full = 0.800, headroom = 0.200)
      shows significant Δr = 0.072 due to more room to improve
    - Detecting Δr = 0.010 would require N = 1050 (impractical)

RECOMMENDATION:
  Document in summary.md Section 3 (Limitations):
    'Source correlation null reflects ceiling effect (r_full = 0.934)
